<p>I have a dataset with several columns and I want to remove all rows if there are duplicates in 3 specified columns.</p>  <p>I've used this code for TWO columns, and it works for that:</p>  <pre><code>mydata2[!duplicated( mydata2[c(1,13)] ),] </code></pre>  <p>BUT, when I try to modify the code by adding another column, like this:</p>  <pre><code>mydata2[!duplicated( mydata2[c(1,8,13)] ),] </code></pre>  <p>I get this error message:</p>  <pre><code>Error in `[.data.frame`(mydata2, c(1, 8, 13)) : undefined columns selected </code></pre>  <p>I know I can select several columns like this: <code>1:5</code>, but the columns with duplicate data are not next to each other.</p>